items.name: Cap of Invisibility
items.description: A cap used by the ancient greeks to become invisible and undetected. Allows you to become Spectral during the daytime, moving undetected, but losing stamina over time. Has no effect at night.Unbreakable.

items.name: Ichthyornis Foot Necklace
items.description: A trophy necklace made of the feet of several Ichthyornis. Wearing this will prevent them from attacking or stealing items from you unless you get too close.

items.name: Pegomastax Claw Necklace
items.description: A trophy necklace made of the claws of several Pegomastax. Wearing this will prevent them from attacking or stealing items from you unless you get too close.

items.name: Thieves Pendant Skin
items.description: Equip this skin on any offhand item to make those thieving Ichthyornis and Pegomastax ignore you.

items.name: Reflect Shield
items.description: An unbreakable shield that reflects 50% of damage back to the attacker.

items.name: Pygmy Armor
items.description: Place this on any Pygmy dino to provide them with some protection

items.name: Saddle Armor
items.description: Place this on tames that do not use saddles to provide them with bonus protection.

items.name: Gravity Boots
items.description:
Unbreakable Boots that make you immune to fall damage and movement impulse, whether it be from damage, knockback, or singularities.

Can double jump while wearing, with a 5-second cooldown.

items.name: Shadow Cloak
items.description:
This piece of cloth armor has been imbued with a Nightmare Soul to make you invisible to enemies at night.
Unbreakable. Consumes 1 stamina per second while worn.

items.name: Void Trousers
items.description:
Pants with the cosmic powers of the void, they make you immune to nearly all environmental effects
Immune to: Gas, Radiation, Enflamed, Heat, Cold, Drowning, and more.

Unbreakable.

items.name: Crystal Poop
items.description: A hefty load of crystal. Can be used as crystal in crafting recipes.

items.name: Element Poop
items.description: A hefty load of element. Can be used as element in crafting recipes and to power a few things that require Element.

items.name: Metal Poop
items.description: A hefty load of metal. Can be used as metal in crafting recipes, and smelted to make ingots.

items.name: Obsidian Poop
items.description: A hefty load of obsidian. Can be used as obsidian in crafting recipes.

items.name: Pearl Poop
items.description: A hefty load of pearl. Can be used as Silica Pearls in crafting recipes.

items.name: Stone Poop
items.description: A hefty load of stone. Can be used as stone in crafting recipes.

items.name: Wood Poop
items.description: A hefty load of wood. Can be used as wood in crafting recipes.

items.description:
Makes you Immortal for 15 seconds. 
You cannot attack while Immortal.

items.name: Dino Beer
items.description:
This fermented liquid courage will reduce the damage your dino takes by 10% and make them immune to Fear, but will also make them gain 1% of their torpor per second and unable to run.

Lasts 60 seconds.

items.description: Grants you stoneskin for 60 seconds, giving you 75% damage reduction.

items.name: Suicide Potion
items.description: Use this to get unstuck from a bad situation.

items.name: Suicide Potion
items.description: Use this to get unstuck from a bad situation.

items.name: Taming Potion
items.description: Instantly Drops the food on a KO dino to zero, making it tame much quicker.

items.name: Unstable Laxative
items.description:
Consuming this item will cause you to lose control of your bowels for a short time. Useful for making Resource variants quickly produce resources in a pinch, or when you need to refill your compost bins or Farming variants.

Warning: Have the health potions ready, you will lose 5% health per second for a full minute while under the effects of this Laxative.

items.name: Vampire Potion
items.description: For 3 minutes, your player will be healed for 100% of the damage it deals.

items.name: Wake-Up Potion
items.description: This potion will instantly wake up any sleeping player. For creatures, it will restore 10% of their maximum torpor per second.

items.name: Pegomastax Claws
items.description: The thieving claws of a Pegomastax.

items.name: Ichthyornis Talons
items.description: Those thieving litlte birds keep taking your items, so you take their feet.

items.name: Alpha Sedative
items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 8x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.name: Beta Sedative
items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 4x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.name: Godlike Sedative
items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 128x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.name: Omega Sedative
items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 64x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.name: Prime Sedative
items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 16x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 2x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.name: Ultimate Sedative
items.description: These powerful sedatives provide 32x the torpor of Narcotics.

items.name: Unique God Soul
items.description: Soul of a Unique Species God. Used to rank up Uniques to Godlike.

items.name: Boss Soul
items.description: Soul harvested from a Boss, used to summon a God.

items.name: God Soul
items.description: Soul of a fallen God. Used to summon something much worse.

items.name: God Soul
items.description: Soul of a fallen God. Used to summon something much worse.

items.name: Omega Soul
items.description:
Soul harvested from a wild Omega creature.
Can be placed in the beacon to guarantee the same variant is summoned.

items.name: Paragon Breaker
items.description:
Dragging a Paragon Soul onto this item will create a Paragon Breaker for that species. You cannot drag a Paragon Soul onto this item inside of a dino's inventory, you must create the Paragon Breaker in the inventory of the player or a structure.

You can feed a Paragon Breaker to a creature that is Paragon level 30 or higher to continue increasing its Paragon Level.

items.name: Paragon Soul
items.description: Place this in the trophy slot of the Omega Beacon to guarantee that your next wild dino summon is a Paragon variant.

items.name: Perfect Soul
items.description:
The soul of Perfect Zodiac.

Feed this to any Ancient tier creature to make it a Zodiac variant.

items.name: Paragon Soul
items.description: Soul harvested from a specific species, used as a permanent power up.

items.name: Unique Group God Soul
items.description:
Soul of one of the Unique Group Gods. 
Can Be used to turn your tame into an ancient tier, or to summon Zodiac.

items.name: Zodiac Soul
items.description:
The soul of Zodiac.

Feed this soul to any Ancient tier group variant creature to make it take the form of a Unique Group God.

items.name: Chest Shard
items.description:
A reward inside of each loot chest. Collect these to prove your chest finding prowess.

Can be used to craft a Golden Chest as a trophy.

items.description:

Its primary use is for crafting kibble, equipment, and potions.
Once unlocked, the Omega beacon can be used to sacrifice souls to attract wild creatures, or even Bosses.

items.name: Alpha Unique Token
items.description:
Feed this to your unique dino to increase its rank from Beta to Alpha. 

This requires a Paragon Soul as a crafting ingredient, and can only be fed to the same species as the Paragon Soul. 

Example: Using a Lystrosaurus Soul to craft this make it only able to be fed to the unique Lystrosaurus, Collider.

items.name: Ancient Unique God Token
items.description:
Use this in the God Egg to summon an Ancient Unique God. Killing the Ancient Unique God will allow you to rank up your Godlike Unique tame to Ancient tier.

The Ancient Unique God summoned by this token will be decided by the Unique God Soul used to craft it. 

IMPORTANT NOTE: Ancient Gods can only be damaged by the same Species! For example, a Reptar God can only be damaged by a Rex. Variants such as Tek, Feathered, and Skeletal do not count and are separate!

items.name: Beta Unique Token
items.description:
Feed this to your unique dino to increase its rank from Basic to Beta. 

This requires a Paragon Soul as a crafting ingredient, and can only be fed to the same species as the Paragon Soul. 

Example: Using a Lystrosaurus Soul to craft this make it only able to be fed to the unique Lystrosaurus, Collider.

items.name: Tameable Boss Token
items.description:
A token used to summon a tameable boss from the beacon. Place this in the trophy slot, and your next summon is guaranteed to be a tameable boss.

NOTE: This Token summons a random tameable boss, using the normal spawn weights to choose a variant.

items.name: Cosmic Tameable Boss Token
items.description: A token used to summon a tameable boss from the beacon. Place this in the trophy slot, and your next summon is guaranteed to be a Cosmic tameable boss.

items.description: Use this to Mind Wipe your dino back to its base tamed level, and return all of the level up points back to redistribute them as needed.

items.name: Eggselerator
items.description: Equipping the Eggselerator in the trophy slot of an Egg Collector will rapidly increase the rate that it is able to generate eggs from surrounding creatures.

items.name: Token of the Fallen God
items.description: Feed this token to your Godlike tame to remove its God powers and return it to an Omega tier.

items.name: Imbue Wipe Token - Armor
items.description: Drag this onto an imbued armor or saddle to wipe the imbues and restore it back to its original settings.

items.name: Imbue Wipe Token - Weapon
items.description: Drag this onto an imbued weapon to wipe the imbues and restore it back to its original settings.

items.name: Soul Furnace Intensifier
items.description: The Intensifier increases the heat at which souls burn and the power generated by them to the point where the Soul Furnace's crafting speed is increased to instant.

items.description:

This requires a Paragon Soul as a crafting ingredient, and can only be fed to the same species as the Paragon Soul. 

Example: Using a Lystrosaurus Soul to craft this make it only able to be fed to the unique Lystrosaurus, Collider.

items.description: Instantly restores all food, but may have other side effects.

items.name: Unstable Water

items.name: Omega Gun

items.name: Cold-weather Shirt
items.description: Keeps you very warm, but only provides a little physical protection.

items.name: Tek Shield
items.description: Highly advanced shield made of pure energy

items.name: BearHug Swim Bottom Skin
items.description:
You can use this to skin the appearance of pants into swim trunks on men or a bikini bottom on women.

Guess that grumpy bruin was hoping for some honey.

items.name: Odd Couple Swim Bottom Skin
items.description:
You can use this to skin the appearance of pants into swim trunks on men or a bikini bottom on women.

They say true love sees but doesn't mind. Good for them!

items.name: Sauropod Heart Swim Bottom Skin
items.description:
You can use this to skin the appearance of pants into swim trunks on men or a bikini bottom on women.

When they form that heart shape, you just feel the love.

items.name: BearHug Swim Top Skin
items.description:
You can use this to skin the appearance of a shirt into a bare chest on men or a bikini top on women.

Love might bear all things, but all bears don't love everything.

items.name: Odd Couple Swim Top Skin
items.description:
You can use this to skin the appearance of a shirt into a bare chest on men or a bikini top on women.

Who are we to deny their love? The heart wants what it wants.

items.name: Sauropod Heart Swim Top Skin
items.description:
You can use this to skin the appearance of a shirt into a bare chest on men or a bikini top on women.

Don't you love it when they curve like that?

items.name: "Self Hug" Emote
items.description:
Consume this to permanently unlock the "Self Hug" emote.

Remember, your survival depends on loving yourself.

items.name: Chromatic Cannon Module
items.description: Chromatic Cannon Upgrade Module

items.name: Chromatic Cannon
items.description: An elementally imbued cannon that is able to use Elemental Souls for power to shoot Elemental Balls. No other ammunition required.

items.name: Craptivator
items.description:
This captivating container of crap can be used to brew up some interesting items. 

Careful, you don't always know what will crawl out of it.

items.name: Gene Splicer
items.description:
This structure allows dinos of different species to mate, assuming that they following the current Breeding Mode server setting. Only the species pre-determined as compatible will be able to mate with this structure, as it will not work for any pair of dinos you want to use.

Originally designed to allow Reaper Kings and Queens to mate, there might also be some interesting combinations when tried with other dinos.

items.name: Cursed Idol
items.description: Curse your items. Do it.

items.name: Dimensional Dumpster
items.description:
A container that can be filled by the vacuum with items you want to destroy.

Place the items inside that you want to store there and press Save, and the Void Vacuum will automatically send those items to that container. Press the Dump button to remove them from the game.

items.name: Dimensional Grinder
items.description:
A storage container able to grind any items inserted into it. 

Place the items inside that you want to store there and press Save, and the Void Vacuum will automatically send those items to that container.

items.name: Dimensional Storage
items.description:
A storage container able to hide a vast number of things in a separate dimension.

Place the items inside that you want to store there and press Save, and the Void Vacuum will automatically send those items to that container.

items.name: Dodo Cage
items.description: Throw a wild Dodo in here to convert it to an unclaimed Dodo, allowing the Egg Collector to generate eggs for it (No-Tame only).

items.name: Egg Collector
items.description:
Place this near your dinos to collect any unfertilized eggs that are dropped on the ground. This will also prevent all unfertilized eggs from spoiling.

The Egg Collector will also passively generate eggs for dinos around in that are in stasis, but will not work with dinos that are attached to a Hitching Post.

items.name: God Egg
items.description:
A massive and mysterious egg. Placing the soul of a dying boss in this egg will cause a God to hatch from it.
BEWARE: God Bosses are late-end game bosses!

items.name: Golden Chest
items.description: A trophy fit for a master chest hunter!

items.name: Omega Item Fragmentor
items.description: Grind up Unique and Set Items as well as Magic Charms into fragments used specifically on those items.

items.name: Charm Fragments
items.description:
Small fragments of a Magic Charm, this item can be used to reroll the imbues on Magic Charms.

Place the Charm in the Omega Upgrade Bench to reroll its imbues. The Bench will tell you the required number of Fragments when clicking on the charm.

items.name: Set Fragments
items.description:
Small fragments of a Set Item, this item can be used to reroll the imbues on Set Items.

Place the Set Item in the Omega Upgrade Bench to reroll its imbues. The Bench will tell you the required number of Fragments when clicking on the Set Item.

items.name: Unique Fragments
items.description:
Small fragments of a Unique Item.

Can be used to Augment Unique Items.

items.name: Omega Altar
items.description:
An ancient altar used to summon powerful gods. 

BE WARNED. Bosses summoned from this are intended to be raid bosses. They should not be attempted without help. They are exponentially stronger and more dangerous than the variant gods and are capable of quickly wiping armies of Omegas.

items.name: Omega Beacon
items.description:
Sacrifices souls to lure in wild creatures to kill or tame. Placing the beacon in the water will summon various water creatures.

Sacrificing 100 souls in the beacon will summon a boss creature, required for progression.

WARNING: DO NOT PLACE THIS NEAR YOUR BASE.
The beacon attracts world bosses, who will spawn at the beacon from time to time, indicated by a large red beam surrounding the beacon. The beacon also destroys structures within a 20-foundation range when used.

items.name: Omega Workbench
items.description: Craft most of Ark Omega's items here!

items.name: Respawn Point
items.description:
Place this anywhere on the map to get an indestructible respawn point with a short cooldown.

Cannot be used for travel.

items.name: Fruit Seeder
items.description: Place berries and crops in here to convert them to seeds.

items.name: Set Item Mannequin
items.description:
Designate a specific set for your mannequin, and the void vacuum will send all of that set here.

Equip a full set to your mannequin, and see the visual bonuses!

items.name: Soul Furnace
items.description:
A structure specifically designed to burn souls for heat. This Furnace has the ability to do the tasks of many other structures. 

Burns Souls for energy.

items.name: Soul Grinder
items.description: Grind Boss and God souls down to get the souls, essence, and soul shards from them.

items.name: Omega Teleporter
items.description: Allows instantaneous transport between Teleporters. Teleporter dinos can be used as mobile remotes to teleport to these from afar.

items.name: Generic Consumable
items.description: Trophy of a Unique Group God.

items.name: Zodiac Trophy
items.description:
A massive trophy to prove that you have beaten Zodiac.

Or have you?

items.name: Unique Totem
items.description:
Store Unique Items Here.

Place one of these near a Void Vacuum, and it will automatically send all Unique items directly to it.

items.name: Imbue Workbench
items.description:
Upgrade your Ark items with Essences from Ark Omega.
Allows random RNG based modifiers to be added to your items that can grant them bonus resistances, damage, armor, durability, etc.

items.name: Kibble Machine
items.description: A machine to craft and store all of your kibble. Will keep them from spoiling.

items.name: Void Vacuum
items.description:
Uses the powerful vacuum of space to draw in and hold any loose items dropped nearby. Will also collect items from bag drops. 

Uses Souls for power.

items.name: Boomstick
items.description: A club capable of spontaneous explosions, dealing damage in a wide area.

items.name: Cloner Staff
items.description: Hitting creatures with this tool will spawn clone for you, whether it be your own tame, or the thing trying to eat you.

items.name: Cosmic Grenade
items.description:
Powerful grenade with cosmic powers. Expensive to craft, to well worth it.
Hold R to bring up the menu to switch between Supernova, Starfire, Singularity, Meteor

items.name: Chromatic Boomerang
items.description: A boomerange imbued with an Elemental Soul, causing random elemental status effects when thrown. The thrown boomerang's damage scales with your melee stat. Cannot be broken.

items.name: Ethereal Spear
items.description: A spear imbued with Ethereal power. Cannot be broken, can be infinitely thrown, and isn't effected by gravity. Thrown damage will scale with both melee damage and movement speed.

items.name: Eviscerator
items.description:
Weapons of rage and hatred. 

The more you attack, the faster you attack.

items.name: Flashbang Grenade
items.description: Bioluminescent Fruit that provides a flash of Charge lighting

items.name: Fortune
items.description:
A golden gilded sword of Luck and Power.

Deals passive damage, bypassing nearly all forms of damage reduction or detection, with a 25% chance to deal triple damage.

items.name: Getaway Orb
items.description:
An orb that is used to summon a Spiritual mount to get you out of a bad situation. The mount cannot be used for combat, and will disappear when dismounted or out of render range.

The mount lasts 30 seconds, with a 60 second total cooldown.

Permanent item, cannot be broken and is not consumed on use.

items.name: Gravitron
items.description:
A blunt weapon made out of just the right amount of alloys and Anti-matter.

Right click will cause Gravitron to pull enemies towards you.

items.name: Hades Torch
items.description: A torch imbued with the mythical power of Hades. Greatly increased light radius, damage, and is unbreakable.

Shooting enemies will Siren them.

items.name: Knockout Club

items.name: Net Gun
items.description:
A small, net-launching gun used to ensnare targets for an extended period. Does not require ammo, and cannot be broken. 

Can trap enemies 50% larger than a Bola, and is much easier to use.

items.name: Multi-Tool
items.description:
A multi-tool able to function as a Pick, Hatchet, Sickle, and Club. 
Use the middle mouse button to toggle between modes. 

Not only bypasses the damage reduction on Resource variants, but deals double damage to them. This can make the Multi-Tool in club mode an extremely effective way to KO low tier Resource creatures.

items.name: Outburst
items.description:
Boom clap, the sound of my heart,
the beat goes on and on and on and on and...

items.name: Phantom
items.description:
The ghost of an infamous deadly hatchet. Curses enemies on attack, making them take more damage.

Can only be equipped at night.

items.name: Plaguefork
items.description: A deadly pitchfork used to help cart away bodies during the plague. Has a chance to inflict Plague while dealing damage.

items.name: Ripper
items.description:
A chainsaw better suited at cutting flesh than cutting trees. Does greatly increased damage, and causes massive bleed damage.

Requires Rage Souls for fuel.

items.name: Risk
items.description: The deadliest gun of all, but its not without downsides.

items.name: Shatter
items.description: A blunt weapon that has been carelessly carved from a block of stone, it has a chance to break off explosives shards that harvest when it hits an object.

items.name: Versatile Slingshot
items.description:
A slingshot with the versatility of firing multiple types of projectiles for various effects. An excellent go-to weapon in a pinch.

Press R to cycle ammunition types.

Stone - Low Damage and Torpor
Metal - Medium Damage and Torpor
Obsidian - High Damage and Torpor
Crystal - High Damage Piercing
Human Feces - Low Damage, Blind, Slow

items.name: Stone Sickle
items.description:
A primitive Sickle used for harvesting fiber and chopping berries off of bushes and shrubs. 

Not very effective in combat.

items.name: Elemental Storm Grenade
items.description:
Grenade that explodes in the elemental storm of your choosing.
Hold R to bring up the menu to switch between Fire, Earth, Ice, Lightning, Water, Wind.

items.name: Stormbringer
items.description:
Swinging this around above your head will surround you in an elemental storm.

Hold R to choose Storm type.

items.name: Thunderbolt
items.description: Charged bolts that deal both lightning damage and cause a Lightning Strike on impact.

items.name: Translocator
items.description: This pick isn't restricted by space or time. Attacking with it will warp you between enemies, striking each of them as you go.

items.name: Undead Sword
items.description: A sword imbued with Nightmarish powers, it can both suck the life out of enemies when dealing damage, and return them as Zombies when killed.

items.name: Eggsecutioner
items.description: A powerful weapon that fires unfertilized eggs for both damage and debuffs.

items.name: Vacuum Grenade
items.description:
This grenades create a poweful vacuum capable of gathering resources from a massive area. Right click (Alt-Fire) to switch between Pick and Hatchet modes.

Pick - Blue
Hatchet - Yellow

items.name: Wabbajack
items.description: A weapon of luck and destruction, the Wabbajack constantly rolls unknown damage modifiers and status effects with each attack.

items.name: Wake-Up Dart
items.description: A dart laced with a powerful stimulant. Will instantly wake up a player, and restore 10% max torpor per second to dinos.

items.name: Warp Bow
items.description:
A bow surging with Cosmic power. Projectiles fired from this bow instantly warp to their target, with no gravity drop or delay.

Hold down R to select ammo type. Uses Knockout Arrows.

Weapon may need to be re-equipped if switching from an empty ammo type.
